Go to the repo https://github.com/nodesource/distributions/blob/master/README.md

and read the instruction for installing node js

for ubuntu systems where you want to install the current version you 

# Using Ubuntu
curl -fsSL https://deb.nodesource.com/setup_current.x | sudo -E bash -
sudo apt-get install -y nodejs

# Using Debian, as root
curl -fsSL https://deb.nodesource.com/setup_current.x | bash -
apt-get install -y nodejs

Now type node --version you should see the version

Optional: install build tools

To compile and install native addons from npm you may also need to install build tools:

# use `sudo` on Ubuntu or run this as root on debian
sudo apt-get install -y build-essential

# for linux Node.js Current (15.x)

# As root
curl -fsSL https://rpm.nodesource.com/setup_current.x | bash -

# No root privileges
curl -fsSL https://rpm.nodesource.com/setup_current.x | sudo bash -
Optional: install build tools

Now type node --version you should see the version

To compile and install native addons from npm you may also need to install build tools:

yum install gcc-c++ make
# or: yum groupinstall 'Development Tools'
